.TH "ring_buffer_resize" 9 "ring_buffer_resize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ring_buffer_resize \- resize the ring buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ring_buffer_resize
.BI "(struct trace_buffer *buffer "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "int cpu_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
the buffer to resize.
.IP "size" 12
the new size.
.IP "cpu_id" 12
the cpu buffer to resize
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Minimum size is 2 * BUF_PAGE_SIZE.

Returns 0 on success and < 0 on failure.
